<h3 class="date"><a href="/2006/sep/04/">&#x27a0;</a> September 4, 2006</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="fairuse4wm_a_wm" >

        
        <a name="002902"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=114916">FairUse4WM - a WM/DRM removal program</a></h4>

        

        <p>I&#8217;ve finally had a chance to test this with files downloaded from Napster and Rhapsody&#8217;s subscription services, and it does what it says on the tin.  The question of interest:  If this could be chained to a transcoder that automagically converted downloads to MP3s that can be played on an iPod, would it cause more customers to sign up for PlaysForSure providers, and damage sales at the iTunes Music Store?</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
